1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,180
The two parts, we have our accuracy and our presentation of the site.

2
00:00:04,260 --> 00:00:06,080
So we'll start off with the accuracy first.

3
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:11,040
So your accuracy is actually scored from a 4.

4
00:00:11,460 --> 00:00:17,780
So from the number 4, you're actually marked during your presentation of your pattern.

5
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,840
And with that one, any mistakes that you make,

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:25,920
whether it's a minor mistake, get a minus of 0.1.

7
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:29,420
If it's a major mistake, get minus 0.3.

8
00:00:29,420 --> 00:00:33,480
So I'll just let you guys know about the difference between the two.

9
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:37,860
So with a minor mistake, it's a very, very small thing.

10
00:00:37,860 --> 00:00:40,480
So say we're doing an outer block.

11
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:44,020
If it's not your shoulder height, maybe it's a little bit lower,

12
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:47,240
or maybe it's a tiny bit higher, that's a minor mistake.

13
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:48,500
So that's a 0.1.

14
00:00:48,980 --> 00:00:52,660
A major mistake would be you're supposed to do an outer block in the pattern,

15
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:55,820
but you forget and you say you do a rich hand strike instead.

16
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:57,780
So that would be a major mistake.

17
00:00:57,780 --> 00:01:02,620
So with a minor mistake, let's say pattern 1, for example,

18
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:04,440
there's 20 steps.

19
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:12,020
It's not uncommon to have up to maybe 14, 15 mistakes in the 20 steps.

20
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:17,540
So the reason for that one being it needs to be absolutely perfect

21
00:01:17,540 --> 00:01:22,220
to not get a deduction of 0.1.

22
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:26,280
So it's not uncommon, let's say, that it's 20 steps

23
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,760
and you made, let's say, 15.

24
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:28,780
So what would that be?

25
00:01:28,780 --> 00:01:34,280
So we'll leave that there on this side, and we'll come back

26
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:36,540
and we'll just calculate the score at the end.

27
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:41,540
So a major mistake, say you're supposed to turn to the left,

28
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:43,860
but you turn to the right, that would be a major mistake.

29
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,920
So obviously, we do want to try and avoid any of these major mistakes.

30
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:53,540
So after we've done our pattern, that's when we move on to the presentation side.

31
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:56,700
So the presentation, as you can see, it's from a score of 6.

32
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:57,760
This is a major mistake.

33
00:01:58,060 --> 00:02:00,480
6 is actually split up into 3 parts.

34
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:02,500
So we have 1, 2, 3 here.

35
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:07,860
So with this one, for a score of 2 is your power and speed.

36
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,540
Your rhythm is also a score of 2,

37
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:14,560
and your expression of energy is also scored out of 2 as well.

38
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:17,380
So we'll start off with the power and speed.

39
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:21,560
So with this one, whether it's your blocks, your kicks, your strikes,

40
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:23,660
your punches, anything that you do,

41
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:27,380
you need to be nice and strong, and it has to be fast as well.

42
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:31,980
So it's one thing to have a very strong punch, or a very fast punch,

43
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:38,380
but it has to be both strong and fast to get high in that category.

44
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:40,380
So the next part is your rhythm.

45
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:44,380
So the rhythm, when you do start your pattern, there is a rhythm to the pattern.

46
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:48,380
It's not just really fast all the way through, it's not slow all the way through.

47
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:52,880
There's a slow, fast, slow, fast kind of aspect to it as well.

48
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:56,980
So you do need to kind of work on your rhythm, and that's also scored out of 2.

49
00:02:57,380 --> 00:03:00,380
The last bit is your expression of energy.

50
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,380
So what is expression of energy?

51
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:08,380
So that's basically how loud you shout, so how much intensity you have during your pattern as well.

52
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:13,380
So say you're doing your pattern really well, it's really fast and it's strong,

53
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:16,380
your rhythm is really great, but you're not shouting very loud,

54
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:21,380
or you can kind of tell, the judges can kind of tell that you're not really confident,

55
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:26,380
you're a little bit nervous, so that's what we need to kind of improve on as well.

56
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:30,380
So I'll just come around to this side.

57
00:03:30,380 --> 00:03:35,380
So with this one, for colour belts and black belts, it's actually scored a little bit differently.

58
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:42,380
So if you're a colour belt, your average, so where the judges actually mark you from,

59
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:46,380
it's actually from a 1.1.

60
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:48,380
So this is your average.

61
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:53,380
So say you did alright, you did average compared to everyone else,

62
00:03:53,380 --> 00:03:56,380
your score for 1, 2 and 3, it'll start from a 1.1.

63
00:03:56,380 --> 00:04:01,380
So if you're less than average in the judges' eyes, you might go down to,

64
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:06,380
say for your power and speed, you might get a 1 or even a 0.9.

65
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:10,380
If you did really great, you might even get a 1.3 or a 1.4.

66
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:16,380
So each individual category, you need to obviously get as high as you can.

67
00:04:16,380 --> 00:04:20,380
If you're a black belt, generally depending on the competition,

68
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:22,380
it will be scored from a 1.3.

69
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:26,380
So 1.3 would be your average that you start from.

70
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:30,380
So say your power and speed was above average,

71
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:36,380
you might get scored a 1.4 for now.

72
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:42,380
Say your rhythm was only about average, it wasn't amazing,

73
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:44,380
it might be just a 1.3.

74
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:48,380
But let's say you didn't shout very loud, so your expression of energy,

75
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:53,380
your average was 1.3, it might drop to, say, a 1.0.

76
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:55,380
So...

77
00:04:56,380 --> 00:04:59,380
This one will come over down to this side.

78
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:05,380
So with this one, as I was saying, it's a total of 10.

79
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:07,380
So that's it.

80
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:13,380
For presentation, we had 1.7, 1, 2, 3.

81
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:15,380
So you had a 3.7.

82
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:18,380
Let's say you made 15 mistakes.

83
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:21,380
So with this one, obviously, don't be too discouraged

84
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:25,380
if you do get pretty high in your mistakes.

85
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:26,380
This is...

86
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:27,380
Three judges.

87
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:30,380
We have three judges usually at the panel.

88
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:32,380
And each judge, obviously, is very subjective.

89
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:37,380
So from their point of view, you might have made a lot of mistakes

90
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:40,380
or you may have made not a lot of mistakes as well.

91
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:44,380
So that's why we have the three judges and we average it out as well.

92
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:46,380
Okay, so...

93
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:51,380
Say we did our 15 mistakes, very small mistakes.

94
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:56,380
So if they're all minus 0.1, it'd be 1.5.

95
00:05:56,380 --> 00:06:04,380
So you go 4.0 minus 1.5, which equals 2.5.

96
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:06,380
So this would be your accuracy score.

97
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:11,380
So with our presentation like before, we're saying we got a 3.7 here.

98
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:16,380
So we add these numbers after the judges are finished scoring.

99
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:23,380
So you would get, for this pattern, a 6.2, which is actually very good.

100
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,380
So I'll just talk a little bit more now about this number.

101
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:34,380
So if you're a color belt, if you're a yellow or above and you do your patterns,

102
00:06:34,380 --> 00:06:43,380
it's not uncommon, generally for a color belt, the average is about a 4 to 5.

103
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:48,380
So if you get a number between 4 and 5 out of 10 for your pattern,

104
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:51,380
that's actually generally considered pretty good.

105
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:55,380
So anything above that, you can consider yourself pretty good.

106
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:58,380
If you're a black belt, the average would say,

107
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:03,380
because we're talking here about the higher presentation as an average,

108
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:12,380
anything from 5 to 6 is actually considered pretty good.

109
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:17,380
And anything over a 7 is actually considered almost world class.

110
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:20,380
So if you get a 7 for any of your patterns,

111
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:24,380
you generally need to pat yourself on the back that you did an amazing job.

112
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:28,380
We just went through our Poomsae scoring.

113
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:31,380
So just remember, accuracy is a 4.0.

114
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:33,380
Presentation is a 6.0.

115
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:37,380
Accuracy is judged during your pattern.

116
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:39,380
Presentation is after.

117
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:42,380
And then we get two scores that we add up.

118
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:44,380
And we get that number.

119
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:49,380
So with this one, obviously, say I was judge number 1.

120
